column5: Got out on the bay this morning.  Beautiful day and managed a 7-noon pass from the misses. Did ok I guess but no big fish.  I went 8 for 10 and 5 of those were cookie cutter short fat 2 pounders (which to me is quite odd as this time of year usually produces 4s and 5s more frequently than 2s). Lost on big fish about 10 ft from the boat and my biggest landed fish was 4.2 pounds. Fish are kind of all over the place right now and I caught fish in water from 12ft to 45ft.  Fun day, just didn't get the weights I was looking for. Fish are getting fat but they are not yet the football they can be.  The next two weeks should be pretty good.
My fav color tube.  Thats a good spot too.  WTG.
nice going  that is a good spot you showed me a few years ago BrianB
lol. I am not saying where that spot is.  Top Secret. lol
Still sounds like good fishin to me. Nothing like the pull of a smallie, big or small!
Good to see you got into some fish Cudz! Like Johnny said, nothing like the pull of some late season bronze! Be seeing you soon!
I wouldn't eat the fish from that spot  Great catch there Cudzs!  Rob C
I'd say looks like not a bad morning Cudz!  Hopefully I'll be able to join you next time.
Thanks for the report.  Hope you get those 5s and 6s when it counts for you!  Kwan
Man I wish I lived closer to that lake. Nice job.
